## Design System Rules for UniFlow mockups

Scope: Static HTML + CSS site using Figma-exported tokens. Follow these rules to keep implementation aligned with design tokens and responsive behavior.

### Token Sources
- Primary token files live in `design-tokens/`:
  - `design-tokens.tokens.json` – canonical tokens (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, radii, containers)
  - `uniflow_variables.json` – currently placeholder
- CSS variable layer is defined at the top of `styles.css` in `:root`. Treat it as a transformation of Figma tokens into runtime variables.

### Core Variables (CSS)
- Colors
  - `--color-white`, `--color-neutral-darkest`, `--color-neutral-darker`, `--color-neutral-dark`, `--color-neutral`, `--color-neutral-light`, `--color-neutral-lighter`, `--color-neutral-lightest`
- Typography
  - Font family: `--font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif`
  - Font sizes: `--font-size-h1 … --font-size-h6`, `--font-size-text-{large,medium,regular,small,tiny}`
  - Line heights: `--line-height-*` matching sizes above
  - Weights: `--font-weight-{light,normal,medium,semibold,bold,extrabold}`
- Layout
  - Containers: `--container-{small,medium,large}`
  - Spacing: `--padding-global`, `--padding-section-{small,medium,large}`
  - Radii: `--border-radius-{small,medium,large}`
  - Shadows: `--shadow-{xxsmall,xsmall,small,medium,large}`

Use these variables exclusively in CSS for colors, spacing, and typography. Do not hardcode pixel values that duplicate tokens unless necessary for algorithmic layout.

### Responsive Rules
- Mobile-first. Breakpoint used: 768px.
- Per workspace rule: on mobile use single-column layout.
- Containers: always wrap sections in `.container` (max-width `--container-large`, horizontal padding `--padding-global`).
- Section vertical spacing: prefer `--padding-section-{medium|large}` depending on prominence.

### Section Patterns
- Section header pattern
  - `.section-header` contains optional `.badge`, `.section-title`, `.section-description`.
  - Badge styling: subtle pill using `--color-neutral-lightest` background and `--color-neutral-dark` text.
  - Titles use heading tokens (H2/H3 typically). Descriptions use `text-regular` or `text-large`.

- Imagery placeholders
  - Use dashed border with `--color-neutral-light`, background `--color-neutral-lightest`, rounded by `--border-radius-large`, and `--shadow-small`.

- Buttons
  - Primary inverse button (dark on light):
    - Background `--color-neutral-darkest`, text `--color-white`, radius `25px`, hover darken to `--color-neutral-darker`.
  - Secondary (ghost) button used in super series:
    - Background `--color-white`, border `1px solid --color-neutral-dark`, hover `--color-neutral-lightest`.

### Existing Components
- Header/nav: responsive hamburger at <768px. Keep menu items in `.nav-menu`, CTA `.nav-cta`.
- Hero: two-column on desktop, single column on mobile. Use H1 tokens and `text-large` for subtitle.
- Accents season: feature cards grid (2 items). Image placeholders follow imagery pattern above.
- Season activities: tabbed dates with `.tab-button` active styling; content wrapper uses dashed border and grid 1fr/1fr on desktop.
- Live trainings (slider):
  - 3 cards per view on desktop (≥1024px), 1 per view on mobile.
  - Use `.slider-container` with internal padding for nav spacing; `.slider-nav` positioned absolutely with 20px inset.
  - No pagination dots (removed by requirement). Navigation only via arrows.
  - Card typography: title uses H5 on desktop, H6 on mobile; body uses `text-regular/small`.
- Super series block:
  - Two-column grid: image left, text right; mobile stacks one-column.
  - Tags are pills as in section badges.
  - CTA is secondary (outlined) button.

### Accessibility
- All interactive controls must include `aria-label`s.
- Maintain color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1. Prefer dark text `--color-neutral-darkest` on light backgrounds.
- Use semantic headings: a single H1 per page, H2 for major sections, H3/H4 for sub-headers.

### Figma ↔ Code Mapping
- Typography mapping:
  - H1..H6 -> `--font-size-h*` and `--line-height-h*`, font-weight bold (700) unless specified.
  - Body text -> `text-{large,medium,regular,small,tiny}` with corresponding line heights.
- Colors:
  - Background -> `--color-white`
  - Text primary -> `--color-neutral-darkest`
  - Muted text -> `--color-neutral-dark`
  - Strokes -> `--color-neutral-light`
- Shadows: choose `{small,medium}` based on elevation; avoid heavier than `large`.

### Authoring Guidelines
- Always use CSS variables from `:root`; if a token is missing, add it to `:root` mirroring `design-tokens.tokens.json`.
- Keep selectors flat; avoid deep specificity.
- Prefer grid/flex for layout, avoid absolute positioning unless necessary.
- Do not reformat unrelated CSS or change indentation.

### Adding New Sections
1. Create semantic `<section class="your-section">` wrapped in `.container`.
2. Reuse `.section-header` pattern when applicable.
3. Use mobile single-column first; add desktop grid in media queries.
4. Derive all spacings and font sizes from tokens.

### MCP/Figma Workflow
- To pull variables: run `#get_variable_defs` with a node selected in Figma (desktop app with MCP).
- When implementing new designs, extract relevant variables and reflect them in `:root` if missing.
- If components are mapped via Code Connect, keep file paths consistent and component names stable.

### File Locations
- Tokens: `design-tokens/`
- Global CSS and variables: `styles.css`
- Markup sections: `index.html`
- Rules: `.cursor/rules/design_system_rules.mdc` (this file)

